\begin{slide}{Routing between the two}
 Join the two networks via a Router
 \begin{itemize}
  \item Router can observe all traffic from any host in one network communicating with any host in another network
  \item Architectural "choke point" \& partitioning tool
  \item Architectural "visibility" enforcement tool
  \item While a firewall is a separate concept, modern routers typicall incorporate firewalls within the same box
 \end{itemize}
\end{slide}

